  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">A suit of trespass brought against William Cairns by Abraham Gesner. Both men had certain mining rights to a deposit of bitumen (albertite) in Albert County, N.B. The case appeared to hinge on whether the deposit was coal and so covered by Cairns&apos; lease. The judge instructed the jury that Cairns&apos; lease included the clause &quot;and other minerals&quot; and that the material in question was certainly a mineral. The jury found in favor of Cairns opining the material was coal--Cf. Dictionary of Canadian biography, v. IX, &quot;Gesner, Abraham&quot;.</subfield>
  </datafield>
